BISHOP Emma Obiorah, of Life of Faith Gospel Assembly Ministries, Onitsha, Anambra State, has lifted widows and the less-privileged with gifts worth N15 million. Two of the widows – Mrs. Mary Obeche and Elizabeth Chukwuma – said they were not thinking of getting such materials Items shared to the people include rice, wrapper, noodles, salt, among others. Bishop Obiorah said his driving purpose was the love of God to mankind. He said in the spirit of Christmas, his church decided to make the people smile again despite the hash economic condition in the country. He said: “I feel happy seeing the smiles on the faces of these widows and the less-privileged. We try to emulate the teachings of Christ and it has to continue. “We call on corporate organisations and wealthy individuals to come to the aid of these people for a better society.”